Package io.github.eingruenesbeb.yolo

Enum Class TextReplacements

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<TextReplacements>
io.github.eingruenesbeb.yolo.TextReplacements
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<TextReplacements>, Constable
public enum TextReplacements extends Enum<TextReplacements>
The TextReplacements enum provides a set of named text replacements that can be used to generate dynamic text in a message. These replacements can be used in chat messages, command responses, or any other text-based content that needs to be customized for a specific player or situation.

Constant names should be pretty self explanatory. If not, you can check their individual documentation.

Here are some examples:

  • %player_name% has used %totem_uses% so far.
  • %player_name% is on hardcore mode!

This enum also provides a helper method, provideDefaults(org.bukkit.entity.Player, io.github.eingruenesbeb.yolo.TextReplacements...), that takes a player object and a list of TextReplacements and returns a hashmap containing the default values for the specified replacements. This can be used to quickly generate replacement values for a given player without needing to manually retrieve their name and totem usage.

    • provideDefaults

      @NotNull public static @NotNull HashMap<String,String> provideDefaults(@Nullable @Nullable org.bukkit.entity.Player player, @Nullable @Nullable TextReplacements... replacements)
      Provides a prefilled HashMap of specified replacements, given the necessary other parameters. The returned map can be directly used, as it is a text-placeholder (String) keyed version.
      Parameters:
      player - The player for whom the replacements should be generated. If null, player-based replacements will not be included in the returned map.
      replacements - The replacements that should be included in the returned map. If null, an empty map will be returned. If the ALL constant is included in this array, it will include all predefined replacements, but should not be used in combination with others.
      Returns:
      A prefilled map of replacements.
      Implementation Note:
      If any necessary reference parameter is not given, replacements referencing it will not be present in the final map. For example, if the player parameter is null, player-based replacements will not be included in the returned map. If the replacements array is null, an empty map will be returned.
